header.gameNote: TOP OF THE WORLD CLASSIC AT FAIRBANKS AK

article.headline: Denver 80, Kennesaw 66
article.story: FAIRBANKS, Alaska (AP) -- DaShawn Walker scored 21 points and Denver defeated Kennesaw State 80-66 Friday in the quarterfinals of the BP Top of the World Classic. Walker and fellow guard Antonio Porch helped Denver (1-0) to a quick early lead over the Owls (0-1). Porch scored eight consecutive points and Walker followed with a pair of 3-pointers to give the Pioneers a 13-point lead just five minutes into the game. Denver pushed the lead to 17 with 13:54 remaining in the first half and led 45-38 at halftime. Kennesaw State used a 12-4 run to start the second half behind seven points by Brent Ragsdale and closed to 51-48 with 16 minutes remaining. But Yemi Nicholson hit a layup and free throw for Denver and two 3-pointers by Walker put Denver up 63-48 with about 9 minutes to play. Walker finished 4-of-7 on 3-point attempts. He pulled down five rebounds and blocked two shots. Nicholson scored 19 points and pulled down nine rebounds. Porch and David Kummer added 13 points each. Golden Ingle led Kennesaw State with 29 points. Ronnell Wooten and Ragsdale added 13 each.
